Enhance Your Scrum Master Skills

The Professional Scrum Master IITM  (PSM II) course is an advanced course helping professionals to understand the stances that characterize an effective Scrum Master and servant-leader. The class teaches about related practices and skills to enable them to have the right types of conversations and how to apply them to become better Scrum Masters.

..... Read more

KnowledgeHut’s new 16-hour advanced PSM II course helps Scrum Masters gain the PSM II credential and develop new skills and enhance their existing ones. The course is specifically designed for experienced Scrum Masters who have a thorough understanding of the Scrum framework. The course teaches students about related practices and skills to enable them to have the right types of conversations and how to apply them to become better Scrum Masters.

It is particularly beneficial for those people with at least one year of Scrum Master experience. Conducted by experienced and certified instructors, this course will help you aim for a first-time pass of the intensive exam and gain the skills to get ahead of the crowd.

The Professional Scrum Master II is a designation offered by Scrum.org™ to practitioners who successfully complete the Professional Scrum Master™ II training and demonstrate their understanding by passing the exam. Professional Scrum Master™ and Scrum.org™ are registered trademarks owned by Scrum.org. KnowledgeHut is a Scrum.org Professional Training Network (PTN) member.

PSM II Training and Certification FAQs

PSM II Training

1. What can I expect to accomplish after completing the PSM II course?

The PSM II course has been thoughtfully designed to make you an exceptional Scrum Master. You will be equipped with all the tools and techniques to:

  • Leverage the knowledge of latest Scrum practices and techniques
  • Learn decision making using Scrum principles
  • Become a servant-leader to teams practicing Scrum
  • Make Development Teams and Product Owners become more effective
  • Lay a framework for Scrum Teams to be more successful  
  • Increase agility by making the environment suitable for Scrum Teams 
2. What practical skills can I expect to have after completing the PSM II course?

Our PSM II training aims to equip you with all the skills to be an effective Scrum Master. You will develop practical skills in the following areas to:

  1. Servant leadership
  2. Facilitation skills
  3. Value creation
  4. Enabling high team performance
  5. Leading and facilitating change
  6. Coaching the Development Team 
  7. Coaching the Organization
  8. Resolving impediments 
  9. Scrum implementation guidance
  10. Enabling Product Increment
3. How does a PSM II certification help me?

The PSM II certification helps you:

  • Validate your commitment to continued excellence and quality. 
  • Demonstrate your proficiency in Scrum 
  • Grow your career in Scrum with confidence.
  • Get noticed at interviews or for promotions at your current job.
  • Command higher salaries than your non-certified peers.
  • Network with industry leaders and Agile professionals 
  • Begin your agile journey to Professional Scrum Master III Certification (PSM III)
4. Is the PSM II course only for software developers?

Not necessarily. Each course has attendees from a variety of backgrounds, including from non-software fields. The instructor will cover product development of all sorts, so many examples are software related, but no software development experience is required.

The course is for anyone interested in learning a better and faster way to create awesome products, including:

  • Business Analysts
  • Developers 
  • Finance and Audit
  • HR Managers
  • IT Professionals 
  • Managers 
  • Product Owners 
  • Project Managers 
  • Project Sponsors 
  • Scrum Masters 
  • Team Leads 
  • Testers 
  • those who are interested in working with people 
  • those who care about their team’s performance 
  • those looking for ways to foster collaboration 
5. What are the prerequisites for this PSM II course?

As this is an advanced course, it is expected that candidates should have prior knowledge on the Scrum framework.

6. What next after PSM II credential?

Once you have completed the PSM II credential, you can further enhance your Scrum Master skills by pursuing the following credentials:

  • Professional Scrum Master III (PSM III)
  • Certified ScrumMaster (CSM)®
7. Are any complementary courses offered with this PSM I Course?

Yes, you will get free e-learning access to over 100 courses that will be available at KnowledgeHut for one year.

8. How many SEUs and PDUs do I earn by completing KnowledgeHut’s PSM II certification training?

You can get 16 PDUs and 16 SEUs by participating in the PSM II training program.

9. What if I have more questions about SEUs and PDUs?

Our blog will help you learn more about how to earn a Scrum Education Unit® (SEU®) from Scrum Alliance®. Get all the information you need to take advantage of SEUs for your professional growth, namely:

  • What are SEUs and why you need them
  • How to earn SEUs
  • What types of continuing education opportunities qualify for SEUs
  • How to calculate the value of an SEU® for Scrum Alliance certifications
  • How to log SEUs for Scrum Alliance® certifications

  • Where you can utilize SEUs you have accumulated

For further information about SEUs and PDUs, please reach us at support@knowledgehut.com.

PSM II Certification Process

1. Who provides PSM II certification?

The PSM II certification is offered by the Scrum.org, a world-renowned body dedicated to helping professionals, leaders, and organizations embrace agile by understanding its principles, processes, and values.

2. Can I get certified without taking the PSM II Course?

You cannot get PSM II certified without undertaking the course. Scrum.org believes that true learning requires in-person/online training and hands-on experience with PSTs or recognized trainers. The PSM II exam is not provided as a substitute for formal training.

3. What is the process to get PSM II certified?

STEP 1: Attend a face-to-face course taught by Professional Scrum Trainer (PSTs) or receive private coaching

OR

Attend 16 hours of live online training with your PST

STEP 2: Upon successful completion of the course, you will receive the exam link with Assessment key from Scrum.org.

STEP 3: Click on the Scrum.org Exam link and take the 60-minute online exam consisting of 80 questions.

STEP 4: Log in with the key and take the 60-minute online exam consisting of 80 questions.

STEP 5: As soon as you complete the online exam and get a minimum score of 85%, you can download the PSM I certification if you have passed the exam.

Note: If the student takes the exam within 14 days (of receiving this email with the password), and scores less than 85%, they are entitled to the 2nd attempt at no cost.

4. When do I get my login information and from whom?

Scrum.org will send you the key post your 16 hours of online training or in-person training.

5. Do you provide a course completion certificate?

Yes, you will receive a course completion certificate on completing the course.

6. How long does it take to get PSM II certified?

You will have to attend two days or 16 hours of PSM II training under a Professional Scrum Trainer (PST) following which you will receive a key to the PSM II exam. Once you pass the exam, you are declared PSM II certified and can instantly download your certificate.

PSM II Certification Exam

1. What is the PSM II exam pattern and passing score?

The PSM II certification exam (also referred to as assessment) is an online, open-book exam. The format is:/p>

  • 80 multiple choice questions and True/False questions
  • Duration: 1 hour
  • Pass mark: 85%
2. What is the difficulty level of the PSM II exam?

The PSM II exam is open-book exam and easy to pass. Our intensive coaching and exam preparation activities are all geared towards helping you pass the exam at the first attempt.

3. Where can I find the link to take the PSM II exam?

After you complete your 16-hour PSM II course, you will receive an email from Scrum.org. This email will contain the key you need to attempt the exam.

4. Will I be able to pause the test and return to it later?

No, you will have a time limit of 60 minutes and will not be able to pause the test. If you accidentally close the window, then you will be able to reopen it immediately. In case your exam page freezes, you can refresh the web browser and you will be able to continue the exam from where you left it. Similarly, if your web browser has a problem, you can go to the start link available in your email and you should be taken back to the last question you were on.

If you lose the internet connection or lose access to the test for an extended time, then you may reach out to support@scrum.org to have a new test set up.

5. If I fail, can I apply for a re-evaluation?

There is no re-evaluation for the PSM II exam. However, if you fail you can re-attempt the exam at no cost within 14 days of receiving the key.

6. Can I retake the PSM I certification test if I fail? How soon?

Yes. The Scrum.org allows you to retake the Professional Scrum Master II exam if you fail. Two attempts are permitted within 14 days after you receive your key, at no additional cost.

7. Can I retake the PSM II exam if I score poorly? How soon?

Yes. The Scrum.org allows you to retake the Professional Scrum Master II exam as many times as you would like. However, there is a cost associated for each attempt beyond the first two attempts within 14 days.

8. How long does it take to receive PSM II exam results?

You will get your results immediately after you attempt the exam.

9. How many attempts do I have to pass the PSM II exam?

There are no limits to the number of times you can attempt the exam, as long as you pay for it. The Scrum.org allows you to take the PSM II exam at no cost for the first 2 attempts within 14 days after you receive your key. Every attempt after that is charged.

PSM II Workshop Experience

1. What are the modes of training offered?

The PSM II workshop at KnowledgeHut is delivered via live and interactive instructor-led training sessions.

Listen, learn, ask questions, and get all your doubts clarified from your instructor, who is an experienced practitioner.

2. How different is the PSM II online training from the conventional in-person training?

The conventional in-person PSM II training from Scrum.org was earlier delivered as a 16-hour training course. The online PSM II training being offered for a limited time is now about 14 hours.

The online course is divided into several classes of shorter hours, unlike the in-person class that has 2 sessions, each 7 to 8 hours long. The PST uses tools like a webcam for interacting with the participants and participants will also be able to virtually collaborate with one another.

3. Who are the instructors?

All KnowledgeHut’s PSM II certification training is delivered by Professional Scrum Trainers (PSTs). The PSTs are:

  • Professionals licensed by Scrum.org to teach the official Scrum.org curriculum
  • Masters in Scrum who have immense experience in leading, applying, coaching, and teaching it
  • Expert practitioners of Scrum across a wide range of industries

Our dedicated team of PSTs deliver high quality training at par with the standards of excellence set out by Scrum.org®. Every candidate receives the same standard of training and content, irrespective of the trainer and the location.

4. How are the workshops structured?

Our PSM II course focuses on engaging interaction. Most class time is dedicated to fun exercises, lively discussions, and team collaboration, all facilitated by an instructor who is a Professional Scrum Trainer and an experienced Scrum practitioner. The focus is on practical solutions to real-world, Scrum Master challenges drawn from decades of experience as product managers, Agile coaches, and Product Owners in Agile environments.

5. What are the software and system requirements?

Software Requirements

  • Internet browser
  • MS Word or Notepad

System Requirements

  • Windows or equivalent environment with Internet browser and high-speed Internet connectivity
6. Are PSM II course materials and workshop instructions provided in advance?

Yes, your PSM II course material will be provided in advance. You will receive an email with a link to set your password a few days in advance of the scheduled course. Once you log in, you will have access to the study plan and all the course material.

7. What PSM II course material will I receive?

The PSM II course material comprises of the course schedule or study plan, workbooks and all relevant assignments, assessments, or case studies.

8. Can I record the PSM II training session?

The PSM II sessions would be auto recorded, subject to permission by Scrum.org® and the PST. Based on the permissions, you would have lifetime access to the video recordings of the sessions as well.

9. Can I use my phone or tab for the training?

No, you will not yet be able to join the training through phone or tab. Please be prepared to join the training on your laptop or desktop.

10. What if I lose internet connection during the training?

If you get disconnected during the training, you will have the option to re-join within about half an hour subject to accreditation body guidelines and the instructor’s preference.

11. Where will the PSM I workshop be held?

Our workshops are currently held online and anyone with a stable internet from anywhere across the world can benefit from this to get PSM™ II certified. You can check out the schedules here.

12. How do I join the PSM II class?

You will receive a registration link for the PSM II workshop to your e-mail id. You can set your password, log in and start your immersive learning journey.

13. What if I miss a class?

If you miss a PSM I class, you may access recordings of the sessions, provided Scrum.org and the PST have permitted recordings. At the beginning of every session, there will also be a 10-12-minute recapitulation of the previous class.

14. Is this a live training, or will I watch pre-recorded videos?

This is a live instructor-led training where you will be coached by Professional Scrum Trainers, authorized by Scrum.org.

15. What platform do you use for video conferencing?

We currently use the Zoom platform for video conferencing and will soon be adding more integrations with WebEx and Microsoft Teams. However, all the sessions and the recordings will be available right from within our learning platform, subject to permission from Scrum.org® and the PST.

16. Will I have other participants in the class?

Yes, there will be other participants who will actively participate in the class remotely. They can attend online training from office, home, or any other suitable place.

17. How does the 24/7 support work?

In case of any queries, our support team is available to you 24/7. You can also reach out to your workshop manager on your workshop group messenger.

18. I have some more doubts. How can I get them cleared?

Should you have any more questions, please email us on support@knowledgehut.com and we will be happy to get back to you.

Finance-related Queries

1. Can I cancel my enrolment? Do I get a refund?

With our 100% Satisfaction Guarantee policy, you are assured of the highest standards of quality. At KnowledgeHut, we strive to ensure that your learning experience with us is beyond reproach. However, if for any reason your expectations are not met, we will refund the course fee in accordance with our 100% Satisfaction Guarantee policy.

2. What is the certification exam fee?

The certification fee for the PSM II exam is not charged separately. Once you enroll for the PSM II certification training with KnowledgeHut, the exam fee is included in the course fee.

3. Is the certification fee inclusive of the course fee?

Yes, the PSM II exam fee is included in KnowledgeHut’s PSM II certification course fee.

4. Is the exam fee refundable?

No, the PSM II exam fee is not refundable. Please speak with your course coordinator for more information.

5. Can I switch my start date?

Yes, you may switch your start date with prior notice of at least 24 hours and subject to availability in the desired batch.

6. Are there any scholarships available?

Yes, scholarships are available for students and veterans with grants that can vary up to 50% of the course fees.

To avail scholarships, please get in touch with us at support@knowledgehut.com. The team shall send across the forms and instructions to you. Based upon the responses and answers that we receive, our panel of experts take a decision on the Grant. The entire process could take about 7 to 15 days.

7. Are there any group discounts?

Yes, group discounts are available and apply to groups as small as three (3) participants. The more participants that attend a training course, the greater the discount. By registering in groups, you can typically save up 20% to 30% on the course fee. For more details, please check out upcoming schedules.

8. Can I pay the course fees in instalments?

Yes, instalment options are available for payment of course fees. To avail the instalment option, please get in touch with us at support@knowledgehut.com. The team will explain how the instalments work and provide timelines for your case. Typically, the number of instalments varies from 2 to 3, but the full amount must be paid before you complete the course.
